After {TURNS()} turns, the hunt ends.
-> END
"
`;

exports[`golden snapshots per fixture (F392) > parse: 23-fox-and-crow.fable 1`] = `
"# title: The Fox and the Crow

VAR cunning = 3
CONST prize = "cheese"

The wood smelled of rain.
-> meeting

=== meeting ===
A crow sat on a branch with a piece of {prize} in her beak.
* (flatter) "What a beautiful voice you must have!"
  The crow puffed up her chest. {cunning > 2: She suspects nothing.|She eyes you warily.}
  * * "Sing for me!" [] The crow opens her beak. -> drop ->
* {cunning > 1} (sneak) Wait quietly [and watch] and watch the branch.
  -> waiting
+ Walk away. # quiet ending
  -> END
- (after) The forest hums. {&Wind stirs.|Leaves fall.|A twig snaps.}
-> waiting

=== waiting ===
Time passes. <>
The cheese {~falls|stays put|wobbles}.
~ cunning = cunning + 1
-> meeting.after

=== drop ===
The cheese tumbles down!
->->
"
`;

exports[`golden snapshots per fixture (F392) > parse: 24-lion-court-epic.fable 1`] = `
"# title: The Lion's Court
# author: Aesop

INCLUDE shared-beasts.fable

VAR favor = 0
VAR tribute = ["honey", "figs"]
CONST king = "Leo"

The summons arrived on a thorn.
-> gates

=== gates === # act: one
Two hyenas flank the gates of {king}'s court.
* {favor >= 0} Present your tribute.
  ~ favor = favor + 1
  {tribute has "honey": The hyenas sniff the honey approvingly.}
  -> hall
* (bribe) Slip the hyenas a fig.
  ~ tribute = tribute - "figs"
  ~ favor = favor - 1
  -> hall
+ Turn back.
  The road home is long. <>
  And it rains.
  -> END

=== hall ===
The hall smells of warm stone. {gates.bribe > 0: A hyena winks at you.}
-> audience ->
The audience over, you exhale.
+ Stay for the feast.
  {&The drums start.|The drums continue.|You stop hearing the drums.}
  -> feast
+ Slip away quietly.
  -> END
* (study) Consult the beast glossary [] first.
  -> beast_glossary
= feast
~ temp courses = RANDOM(3, 7)
{courses} courses! Your favor stands at {favor}.
-> END

=== audience ===
{king} regards you {favor > 0: warmly|coolly}.
"Speak," he rumbles.
* "I bring news of the river." [] You tell him of the drying ford.
  ~ favor = favor + 2
* "I seek your judgement." [] You lay out the jackal's claim.
  ~ favor = favor + 1
* Say nothing.
- He waves a paw, satisfied or not.
->->
"
`;

exports[`golden snapshots per fixture (F392) > parse: shared-beasts.fable 1`] = `
"=== beast_glossary ===
A reference of every beast at court.
-> END
"
`;

